the system for business automation (sba): programming language.wthe system for business automation (sba) is a systemwithin which application experts-nonprogrammers-can describe and execute their applications on a computer. the user of sba views his application as manipulation of information in two-dimensional pictures of tables,business forms, and reports on a display terminal.  he can gradually automate this application by giving "examples"to the system of how he manually manipulates the information.  the query-by-example database languageis a subset of the sba programming language.cacm june, zloof, m. m.de jong, s. p..kprogramming language, graphics, user in terface,data flow, forms flow, data abstraction, database, query, data processing, business system specification, application programming.c. . . . .ca jb december ,   : am